what are your favourite ways to give someone a non body based compliment?
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it's my favourite way to compliment my friends and family! people are so much more than their body! 
compliments are free, from the heart and have the #PowerToTransform someone’s mood! I’m excited to partner with @Pantene on this campaign because I truly believe compliments have the power to transform someone’s day.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments actually go a long way in CONNECTING ourselves to others. A @pantene study found that 77% of canadians have felt disconnected from their friends and family during this time and yet 79% of canadians found a compliment can go a LONG way to making them feel better.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments that are genuine are never superficial and never get old. on top of that, we should be giving them to ourselves too! 
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
make someone's day a bit brighter! #PowerToTransform #partner #ad

Girls from across the world have written an open letter to Instagram, Facebook, TikTok and Twitter, calling on them to create stronger and more effective ways to report abuse and harassment. node.text: my general take on what’s happening as of now. of course i didn’t get to say everything that i wanted to say and didn’t say everything right. it is a WILD time that we are living in. be prepared to be uncomfortable. be grateful we all still have internet, running water and food. (some of us actually still don’t have those things) and most of all, be grateful we have each other. it sounds corny as hell, but you don’t have your food or toilet paper or internet or water without the help of another human. don’t buy 250 rolls of toilet paper, it’s not the diarrhea boogeyman coming for you. also, what happens after this? do we go back to normal life? will there be a normal life? do you even WANT your normal life back? this is going to be a huge shift for many of us. your emotional shit is going to come up because we don’t have the same comforts as before. be kind and stay vigilant and stay aware! ✌️💕

node.text:
i get asked sometimes how i’ve come to the point of being mentally stable and happy and all the things.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the question always makes me a bit quiet. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
here is a journal entry i wrote back in 2012 (swipe.)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“i hate you writing, what have you done for me?
i’m not good at anything. i can't even put pictures onto paper and some sort of semblance to make anything look good. i am messy and disorganized and incomplete.
everything can go fuck off.
i want to take my mind / past and spit on it. you fucking suck. you are shit. you are inconsistent and unintelligent. you bother me and break my heart. i hate myself because of you. i hate myself because of myself. when i feel this way no moment that ever felt good exists. there is nothing stronger in the world than my desire to destroy who i am. it makes sense. it makes sense.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
love and happiness are not final destination points. i STILL have moments of feeling like this. i still feel the pull of hate and contempt and i still burn with anger that at times feels like it has raged on for 1000’s of sunrises. i still wake up with a deep desire to hurt myself and others so i can express what i don’t have language for.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i make a choice every day to try my best. i make a choice to try and be curious and honest and to feel things and communicate them.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s never been easy but it does get easier.
i have hope for you 🌱💕
#hatetolove
#selfgrowth
#mentalhealth
📸 - @jennahill.co

node.text:
i get this question a lot in private.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“how can i reveal myself more?
what if they don’t like what they see?
how did you do it?
i’ve never let anyone see me in the light.
i don’t think they will accept me.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
first things first, anyone who wants to be with you physically has LOOKED at you. like, really looked! and they obviously like what they see and nothing else about you will turn them off. and in the rare instance that it does, it’s their problem. not yours. forever not yours.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
communicating with partners about what makes us feel insecure is important. and also what makes us feel desired. if there are certain ways you want to be desired that you feel too insecure to initiate, take little steps and ask for your partners help.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
find out what makes you feel free and liberated. just because this is tender and difficult doesn’t mean that it’s impossible. it just means it might take a while.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
there’s also no rush whatsoever. honouring where you’re at while also wanting to be somewhere different is a whole thing ❤️🔥
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
you deserve to be seen and to be loved.

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
did you hear any of these growing up?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the “quit being so sensitive” one ruined me. i was so sensitive and anxious growing up it was like i couldn’t turn off my alarms or my imagination. which are both some how connected. my sensitivity gave me access to creativity, empathy and depth of experience. i didn’t just like people i loved them. i didn’t just enjoy nature, i could feel it in every part of my body. there was never just one story in my head but thousands. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but the same was true for pain. it was never just “goodbye see you next week” it was “what if next week never comes?” “what if you didn’t show up like that one time?” if someone at school didn’t like me it was the end of my world. if it was pain on some part of my body, my whole being felt it instead. i couldn’t turn it off.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s only been in the last few years that’s i’ve learned that sensitivity isn’t a bad thing, especially once you are able to regulate and have a dialogue with it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but holy fuck. was it ever stigmatized with the whole “quit being so sensitive.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i also go the “you’re so dramatic” and “you make a big deal out of everything.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
little by little, we undo what was said and done 🪡 🧵
via @sitwithwhit
